Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.14,0:00:11.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1995年，宾州匹兹堡的警方正为两桩银行劫案挠头，案子多少有点蹊跷
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.14,0:00:11.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In 1995, police in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania were investigating a pair of bank robberies that struck them as somewhat odd.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:11.55,0:00:13.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这两起劫案显然是团伙作案
Dialogue: 1,0:00:11.55,0:00:13.20,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The bank robberies were related 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.20,0:00:18.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,监控录像显示，作案的是同一拨人，手法也如出一辙
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.20,0:00:18.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,in that security footage had captured the same two men committing both in the same manner.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.87,0:00:23.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一人排队望风，另一人则掏出手枪直指出纳
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.87,0:00:23.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,One would wait in line, acting as a lookout, while the other stuck up the teller with a handgun.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.92,0:00:27.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,两起案子下来，这伙人卷走了几千美刀
Dialogue: 1,0:00:23.92,0:00:27.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In both robberies, the men made off with a few thousand dollars.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.80,0:00:30.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这抢劫手法嘛，实在算不上高明
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.80,0:00:30.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Not the most sophisticated of heists, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:30.55,0:00:34.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且监控还把俩人拍得一清二楚
Dialogue: 1,0:00:30.55,0:00:34.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which paired with the fact the men were clearly recognizable in the footage,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.26,0:00:37.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们似乎压根没想过要遮掩身份
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.26,0:00:37.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and seemingly made no attempt to conceal their identities, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:37.65,0:00:41.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这让警方觉得，事情背后必有蹊跷
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.65,0:00:41.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,made it seem like there might be something more to this.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.00,0:00:44.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,银行职员也确认，这俩人的脸看得真真儿的
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.00,0:00:44.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The bank staff confirmed the men's faces were plainly visible.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.80,0:00:49.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,没戴丝袜头套，没戴墨镜，也没贴假胡子
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.80,0:00:49.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They weren't wearing tights, or sunglasses, or fake mustaches, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.12,0:00:54.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,看上去也不像戴了假发或化了妆，啥掩饰都没有
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.12,0:00:54.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and it didn't seem like they had wigs, or makeup, or anything like that.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:54.27,0:00:55.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这么简单粗暴的抢劫
Dialogue: 1,0:00:54.27,0:00:55.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,For such straightforward robberies, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.96,0:01:00.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,怎么着也得来个经典的巴拉克拉法帽加卫衣的标准套餐吧
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.96,0:01:00.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,you'd think they'd just have the classic balaclava and hood combo.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:00.04,0:01:07.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,更诡异的是，这俩人似乎还特意冲着监控摄像头露出了微笑
Dialogue: 1,0:01:00.04,0:01:07.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Even stranger, the men had seemingly made a point of looking directly at the security cameras and smiling.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.22,0:01:08.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这到底演的是哪一出
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.22,0:01:08.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,What the hell was going on?
Dialogue: 2,0:01:08.88,0:01:10.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,案发几天后
Dialogue: 1,0:01:08.88,0:01:10.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,A few days after the robbery, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.60,0:01:12.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,警方逮捕了克利夫顿·约翰逊
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.60,0:01:12.58,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,police arrested Clifton Johnson, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:12.58,0:01:17.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这家伙因去年的另外两起抢劫案正在被通缉
Dialogue: 1,0:01:12.58,0:01:17.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who was wanted in connection with two other robberies that had taken place the previous year.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.97,0:01:23.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,警方很快意识到，约翰逊就是最近这起劫案里那个露着大脸望风的家伙
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.97,0:01:23.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Police soon realized that Johnson was the plain-faced lookout in the recent bank robberies, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.68,0:01:25.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他自己也供认不讳
Dialogue: 1,0:01:23.68,0:01:25.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and he admitted it.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.54,0:01:31.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,嘿，这可真是得来全不费工夫，看来他们还真是“素颜”抢银行啊
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.54,0:01:31.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Huh. Well, that was easy. I guess they really did just rob a bank with no disguise.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.04,0:01:33.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那要抓到那个持枪的同伙，应该也不难吧
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.04,0:01:33.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Shouldn't be too hard to find the gunman, then.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.22,0:01:36.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但几个月过去了，案子毫无进展
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.22,0:01:36.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But several months passed with no further arrests, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.35,0:01:43.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,警方最终只好把枪手的照片放到了本地新闻的《匹兹堡犯罪克星》节目上
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.35,0:01:43.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and eventually the police released a photo of the gunman on Pittsburgh Crime Stoppers, a segment on the local news.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.32,0:01:47.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,匿名举报蜂拥而至，节目播出不到一小时
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.32,0:01:47.74,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Anonymous tips poured in, and within an hour of the broadcast, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:47.74,0:01:50.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,警方就逮捕了麦克阿瑟·惠勒
Dialogue: 1,0:01:47.74,0:01:50.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,police had arrested McArthur Wheeler, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.04,0:01:53.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他跟监控录像里的劫匪长得一模一样
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.04,0:01:53.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who was a striking match with the robber on the surveillance footage, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.88,0:01:56.05,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且名字也蠢得可以
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.88,0:01:56.05,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and also had a stupid name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.88,0:01:58.29,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,麦克阿瑟一般作为姓使用
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.05,0:01:58.29,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,麦克阿瑟，当做名字
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.05,0:01:58.29,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,McArthur, as a first name. 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.29,0:02:01.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,Mc这个词根在盖尔语里是“儿子”的意思
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.29,0:02:01.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The Mc part of these names is short for the Gaelic Mac, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:01.94,0:02:06.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,就像罗纳德，唐纳德之子
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.94,0:02:06.14,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which means son, as in Ronald, son of Donald.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.14,0:02:09.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,所以麦克阿瑟根本就不算个正经名字
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.14,0:02:09.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,So McArthur doesn't even really have a name. 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.15,0:02:13.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他只是“阿瑟之子”，我就纳闷他爹妈到底有谁叫阿瑟吗
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.15,0:02:13.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He's just son of Arthur. I wonder were either of his parents even named Arthur?
Dialogue: 2,0:02:13.88,0:02:19.93,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,闲话少说，当麦克阿瑟·惠勒看到自己持枪抢银行的清晰影像时
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.88,0:02:19.93,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Anyways, when MacArthur Wheeler was shown images of what appeared to be a very clearly identifiable him 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.93,0:02:25.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他整个人都懵了，脸上写满了困惑与绝望
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.93,0:02:25.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,robbing a bank with a gun, his response was one of confusion and despair.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:25.45,0:02:26.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他说
Dialogue: 1,0:02:25.45,0:02:26.43,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He said,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.43,0:02:30.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,可是我涂了柠檬汁啊，我明明涂了柠檬汁
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.43,0:02:30.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But I wore the lemon juice. I wore the lemon juice.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.50,0:02:33.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,好吧，哥们，这家伙到底在说什么啊
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.50,0:02:33.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Alright, well, what are you talking about?
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.36,0:02:40.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,惠勒解释说，是约翰逊说服他用一个天才计划去抢银行，保证能逍遥法外
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.36,0:02:40.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Wheeler explained that Johnson had convinced him of a genius plan to rob the banks and get away with it.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.64,0:02:43.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,约翰逊的妙计就是，柠檬汁
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.64,0:02:43.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Johnson's idea was lemon juice.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:43.64,0:02:48.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你懂的，就是你小时候学到柠檬汁可以当隐形墨水
Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.64,0:02:48.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,You know when you're a kid and you learn lemon juice can be used as invisible ink, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:48.38,0:02:50.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后你就一辈子都记着这个冷知识
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.38,0:02:50.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and then remember it for the rest of your life,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.30,0:02:55.08,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,because when you're a kid you're certain that will one day prove invaluable information.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.35,0:02:55.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,坚信这玩意儿有朝一日必成大器
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.08,0:02:59.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,显然，克利夫顿·约翰逊对这个知识点的记忆出了点偏差
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.08,0:02:59.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Well, Clifton Johnson had obviously not remembered this very well, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.12,0:03:05.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他不知怎么就以为，既然柠檬汁能用来写密信
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.12,0:03:05.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,as he was somehow under the impression that just as lemon juice could be used to write hidden messages,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.15,0:03:08.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那它肯定也能在监控录像里“隐形”
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.15,0:03:08.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,it would also be undetectable in surveillance footage.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:08.92,0:03:13.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,恕我直言，他大概是觉得，你根本没法给柠檬汁拍照，是这意思吧
Dialogue: 1,0:03:08.92,0:03:13.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Basically, he thought it was impossible to take a picture of lemon juice, I guess?
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.85,0:03:19.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我猜他可能是摸到点门道了，意思是，你能在这张图里看见柠檬汁吗
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.85,0:03:19.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I suppose he was sort of onto something. I mean, can you see any lemon juice in this picture?
Dialogue: 2,0:03:19.24,0:03:19.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不行吧
Dialogue: 1,0:03:19.24,0:03:19.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,No, 
Dialogue: 2,0:03:19.88,0:03:25.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但约翰逊不知怎地就认为，柠檬汁能把它涂抹的任何东西都遮盖掉
Dialogue: 1,0:03:19.88,0:03:25.21,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but Johnson somehow thought that the lemon juice would obscure whatever it was smeared on.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:25.21,0:03:27.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,放在这个案子里，就是劫匪的脸
Dialogue: 1,0:03:25.21,0:03:27.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In this case, the bank robbers' faces.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.44,0:03:30.96,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,惠勒告诉警方，他一开始也不信约翰逊
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.44,0:03:30.96,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Wheeler told police he didn't initially believe Johnson.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:30.96,0:03:33.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,麦克阿瑟，你看人真准
Dialogue: 1,0:03:30.96,0:03:33.04,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,That's a good instinct, McArthur.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.04,0:03:39.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但他还是往自己脸上抹了点柠檬汁，然后用拍立得给自己拍了张照
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.04,0:03:39.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But that was until he put some lemon juice on his face and then took a Polaroid picture of himself.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.88,0:03:42.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,照片上，他还真消失了
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.88,0:03:42.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,He was absent from the photo.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.73,0:03:48.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这下他深信不疑，立马伙同约翰逊，顶着一脸柠檬汁去抢银行了
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.73,0:03:48.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This convinced him to join Johnson in robbing banks with lemon juice smeared on his face.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.68,0:03:53.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,警方也搞不明白，惠勒的实验是怎么“成功”的
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.68,0:03:53.20,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Police could not account for how Wheeler's experiment was a success.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.20,0:03:58.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,废话，最大的可能就是他瞎搞一气，根本没把自己拍进镜头里
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.20,0:03:58.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Well, other than the likelihood that he had made up balls of it and just not been in frame.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.28,0:04:01.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也许是柠檬汁辣了眼睛，他压根没看清
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.28,0:04:01.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Maybe he'd gotten lemon juice in his eyes and couldn't see right.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.90,0:04:03.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也许他就是个纯粹的啥比
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.90,0:04:03.56,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Maybe he was just an idiot.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.56,0:04:07.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,好吧，故事讲到这份上，他是不是啥比这事儿，已经毋庸置疑了
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.56,0:04:07.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Well, I guess at this point in the story, his idiocy is beyond question.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.26,0:04:13.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,法庭上，克利夫顿·约翰逊当庭指证了麦克阿瑟·惠勒，自己喜提五年监禁
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.26,0:04:13.45,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,In court, Clifton Johnson testified against McArthur Wheeler and received a five-year prison sentence.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.45,0:04:16.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,惠勒则被判了24年
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.45,0:04:16.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Wheeler went to prison for 24 years.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.59,0:04:19.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,约翰逊这家伙听起来可真是个泌阳的
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.59,0:04:19.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This Johnson guy sounds like a real jerk.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.02,0:04:25.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,几年后，社会心理学家大卫·邓宁读到了这个柠檬汁劫匪的故事
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.02,0:04:25.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,A couple years later, David Dunning, a social psychologist, was reading about the story of the lemon juice robbers
Dialogue: 2,0:04:25.27,0:04:26.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他得出一个结论
Dialogue: 1,0:04:25.27,0:04:26.94,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and came to the conclusion, 
Dialogue: 2,0:04:26.94,0:04:29.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如果说惠勒蠢到不配当个劫匪
Dialogue: 1,0:04:26.94,0:04:29.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,if Wheeler was too stupid to be a bank robber, 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.94,0:04:33.67,Yahei-1920x1080,atg3,0,0,0,,蠢货！两个可以进博物馆的蠢货
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.31,0:04:33.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,那他可能也蠢到意识不到自己有多蠢
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.31,0:04:33.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,perhaps he was also too stupid to know that he was too stupid to be a bank robber.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.67,0:04:39.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也就是说，他的愚蠢，反而让他对自己的愚蠢浑然不觉
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.67,0:04:39.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,That is, his stupidity protected him from an awareness of his own stupidity.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:39.26,0:04:45.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,1999年，他和他的研究生贾斯汀·克鲁格合著了一篇论文，标题是
Dialogue: 1,0:04:39.26,0:04:45.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,With his graduate student, Justin Kruger, he authored a paper in 1999 entitled,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.15,0:04:47.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,《既无能，且无知》
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.15,0:04:47.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Unskilled and Unaware of It.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:47.16,0:04:53.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,副标题是《论认知自身无能的困难，如何导致了过高的自我评估》
Dialogue: 1,0:04:47.16,0:04:53.18,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,How difficulties in recognizing one's own incompetence lead to inflated self-assessments.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.18,0:04:57.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,核心思想就是，当你无知时，你甚至都不知道自己有多无知
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.18,0:04:57.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's basically about how, when you're ignorant, you don't even know how much you don't know.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.87,0:05:00.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比如，如果我想做个游戏
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.87,0:05:00.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Like, if I wanted to make a video game, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:00.30,0:05:07.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我对编程和3D建模略知一二，所以我知道这背后有太多我不懂的东西得学
Dialogue: 1,0:05:00.30,0:05:07.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I know enough about programming and 3D modeling to know that there are things I don't know and would have to learn.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.00,0:05:11.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比如动画绑定要刷权重，还有UV展开之类的
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.00,0:05:11.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Like weight painting for the animation rig, or UV unwrapping.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:11.77,0:05:16.63,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因此，要说我能做个好游戏，我自己都没啥信心
Dialogue: 1,0:05:11.77,0:05:16.63,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Therefore, I would have pretty low confidence I could make a good video game.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.63,0:05:22.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但那些甚至不知道这些门道存在的人，大概会觉得这事儿比想象中简单多了
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.63,0:05:22.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But someone who doesn't even know that stuff exists, probably thinks there's much less to learn than there actually is.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.42,0:05:26.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们八成就是那种天天对开发者指点江山，说“你照某某做不就完了”的人
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.42,0:05:26.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And is probably in the habit of telling game developers to just do X.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.78,0:05:30.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这类人总觉得，出点子才是最难的
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.78,0:05:30.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The sort of person who thinks coming up with the ideas is the hard part.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.48,0:05:33.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,水平有多低，信心就有多高
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.48,0:05:33.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Minimal competence, maximum confidence.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:33.31,0:05:37.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这就是著名的“邓宁-克鲁格效应”，你以前可能听说过
Dialogue: 1,0:05:33.31,0:05:37.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This is known as the Dunning-Kruger effect, which you may have heard of before.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.92,0:05:39.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我觉得这故事最吓人的地方在于
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.92,0:05:39.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,I think the scariest part of this story 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:39.80,0:05:44.63,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,约翰逊和惠勒的行为，仅仅被归类为普通的人类愚蠢行为
Dialogue: 1,0:05:39.80,0:05:44.63,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,is that Johnson and Wheeler's actions are just considered regular old human stupidity.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:44.63,0:05:48.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,仿佛“柠檬汁能让摄像头发瞎”
Dialogue: 1,0:05:44.63,0:05:48.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Like, it's normal to think lemon juice makes things invisible to cameras, 
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.44,0:05:50.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,或者“我是第一个想到这招的天才”这种想法，都很正常
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.44,0:05:50.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,or that you're the first person to think of this.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:50.48,0:05:58.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并且还对此迷之自信，甚至敢为此赌上后半辈子去抢银行
Dialogue: 1,0:05:50.48,0:05:58.14,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And to be so confident in this that you'd be willing to engage in such high stake risk as robbing a bank on the back of it.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:58.14,0:06:02.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,对我来说，这太反常了，这已经不是典型的人类失误了
Dialogue: 1,0:05:58.14,0:06:02.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,To me, that's abnormal. Like, that's not just typical human error. 
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.65,0:06:05.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这简直是严重的认知障碍
Dialogue: 1,0:06:02.68,0:06:05.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,That's like, a serious impairment.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:05.35,0:06:09.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我只能理解为，这俩人要么是嗨大了
Dialogue: 1,0:06:05.35,0:06:09.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It only makes sense to me that these guys were massively drug-addled, 
Dialogue: 2,0:06:09.07,0:06:12.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,要么就是那种你真的不该嘲笑他们“愚蠢”的人
Dialogue: 1,0:06:09.07,0:06:12.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,or they're the sort of people that you really shouldn't call stupid.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:12.07,0:06:13.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你懂的，这不好笑
Dialogue: 1,0:06:12.07,0:06:13.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,You know, that's not funny.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.79,0:06:16.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,关键是社会居然认为他们的智力在“可接受”范围内
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.79,0:06:16.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The idea that they fall under an acceptable tolerance of intelligence, 
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.92,0:06:20.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,允许他们无人监管地生活
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.92,0:06:20.28,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that society allows them to live their lives unsupervised,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:20.28,0:06:24.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还能像我们其他人一样，被司法系统正常起诉
Dialogue: 1,0:06:20.28,0:06:24.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and be prosecuted by the justice system like any of the rest of us.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:24.12,0:06:27.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这事儿啊，在很多层面上都让人细思极恐
Dialogue: 1,0:06:24.12,0:06:27.64,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Now, that is concerning on many levels.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:27.64,0:06:32.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,算了，对于用柠檬汁抢银行这种事，咱们还是别想太深了
Dialogue: 1,0:06:27.64,0:06:32.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Well, best not to think too deeply about bank robberies committed with lemon juice.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.07,0:06:34.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不如多看看我的其他视频
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.07,0:06:34.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Instead, watch more of my videos. 
Dialogue: 2,0:06:34.31,0:06:37.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,风格类似，但主题各异
Dialogue: 1,0:06:34.31,0:06:37.40,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They're similar to this one, but cover different topics.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:37.40,0:06:39.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,嘛，这话你大概也猜到了
Dialogue: 1,0:06:37.40,0:06:39.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Well, you probably could have guessed that.
